According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Aircraft ACMI Leasing market was valued at USD 4.69 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 7.68 billion by 2032, expanding at a CAGR of 7.5% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing steady growth as airlines increasingly adopt Aircraft, Crew, Maintenance, and Insurance (ACMI) leasing solutions to enhance operational flexibility, manage seasonal demand, and expand fleet capacity without significant capital investment. Growing passenger traffic, booming e-commerce-driven air cargo demand, and the industry's shift toward asset-light business models are key factors supporting market expansion.
